The Presidency says it appreciates the public’s desire to see an urgent resolution to the suspension of SARS Commissioner Tom Moyane. This after the National Treasury announced that Mark Kingon will act in Moyane’s position. Kingon was the acting chief officer of business and individual tax after Jonas Makwakwa announced his resignation from the position last week. Presidential spokesperson Khusela Diko says the urgent restoration of confidence in SARS is in the public interest. Click to listen: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/542388">Content hosted by iono.fm</a> About SABC View all posts by SABC